00:40:28,159 --> 00:40:30,360
But you are hiding, Owen.

482
00:40:36,399 --> 00:40:38,639
Get in the cage.

483
00:40:41,959 --> 00:40:44,160
Not if you're gonna
point a gun at me.

484
00:40:44,160 --> 00:40:45,600
Do you want me to shoot you?

485
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:48,439
Lower the gun.

486
00:40:48,439 --> 00:40:52,960
And then I will get into the cage.

487
00:41:22,759 --> 00:41:24,999
Good boy.

488
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:32,640
What's the longest anyone's been
in there? That'd be Dan Hodges.

489
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:37,159
when you're up close with it, take
a look into its eyes. Open the door!

490
00:41:40,680 --> 00:41:45,839
It's like looking into the
darkest recesses of your own soul.

491
00:41:45,839 --> 00:41:48,799
Open the door!

492
00:43:01,759 --> 00:43:03,120
Owen!

493
00:43:04,879 --> 00:43:07,320
I said open the door!

494
00:43:07,320 --> 00:43:08,239
Jack!

495
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,560
Open it!

496
00:43:15,240 --> 00:43:16,999
Owen? Get off me!

497
00:43:18,279 --> 00:43:21,039
That's enough!
Help me, Jack, help me get him out!

498
00:43:21,039 --> 00:43:23,839
Owen, come on... Get a stretcher!

499
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:36,999
You did this to him. He did it
to himself, he had no fear.

500
00:43:43,080 --> 00:43:47,599
It's over now.
These creatures are to be left alone.

501
00:43:47,599 --> 00:43:50,680
Go back to your lives. Jack!

502
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:58,560
What're you doing? It's over.

503
00:44:09,400 --> 00:44:14,200
THE MAN WRITHES IN AGONY

504
00:44:26,359 --> 00:44:28,159
You shouldn't have.

505
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:32,040
No, really you shouldn't.
I hate grapes.

506
00:44:35,279 --> 00:44:37,519
Doctors reckon you can go home.

507
00:44:39,119 --> 00:44:41,640
Doctors. What do they know, eh?

508
00:44:45,439 --> 00:44:47,919
I didn't want saving.

509
00:44:50,919 --> 00:44:52,879
You want us to apologise?

510
00:44:52,879 --> 00:44:56,160
For a few seconds in that cage,

511
00:44:56,160 --> 00:45:00,600
I felt totally at peace.

512
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:05,560
And then you blunder in.

513
00:45:08,640 --> 00:45:10,920
Do you always know best, Jack?

514
00:45:12,480 --> 00:45:14,799
Is that what you believe?

515
00:45:14,799 --> 00:45:18,120
Want you back in work tomorrow.

516
00:45:29,359 --> 00:45:33,000
You sure you'll be all right?
Give us a moment alone, yeah?

517
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:39,439
Where's the SUV?
Has it been stolen?

518
00:46:39,439 --> 00:46:41,760
No, we have.

519
00:46:41,760 --> 00:46:45,240
They're stuck in the middle
of the Cardiff Blitz! Toshiko!

520
00:46:45,240 --> 00:46:47,200
It's our duty to get them out.

521
00:46:47,200 --> 00:46:50,799
Open the rift now and the
whole world could suffer.
Or who knows what will come out?

522
00:46:50,799 --> 00:46:52,399
I love you.

523
00:46:52,399 --> 00:46:55,759
It's a trap to
incite total chaos and destruction!

524
00:46:55,759 --> 00:46:59,880
You don't even know who he is!
He's our leader. Not any more!

525
00:46:59,959 --> 00:47:02,520
Captain Jack Harkness,
133rd Squadron.

